 cultural project was tightly linked to party educational institutions. He provides the first account of the early history and politics of three major institutions founded after the Revolution: Sverdlov Communist University, where the quest to transform everyday life gripped the student movement; the Institute of Red Professors, where the Bolsheviks sought to train a new communist intellectual or red specialist; and the Communist Academy, headquarters for a planned, collectivist, proletarian science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aCommunism and culturezSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aCommunism and educationzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aEducation, HigherzSoviet UnionxHistory. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook Package Archivez978311053617108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501705397zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501705397zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501705397.jpg  a978-3-11-053617-1 COR eBook Package Archive  a978-3-11-066749-3 COR eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA